INSERT INTO `ra_issues` VALUES (763,1,50,'Accommodate audit trails into day-to-day operation','1. Add MySQL triggers\r\n2. Is it possible to add custom messages for each change, also containing the user that initiated the change? This needs to be done via PHP, but if using MySQL triggers you lose the connectivity between PHP and MySQL.\r\n3. Change Laravel code to accommodate the history tables.',NULL,NULL,5,29,4,NULL,2,5,'2014-08-03 16:18:22','2014-12-18 11:43:22','2014-08-03',0,NULL,NULL,763,1,2,0,'2014-12-18 11:43:22'),(767,2,50,'Named routes','All routes should have it\'s own names.\r\n\r\nRight now only GET routes have names, but POST routes should have names too. The same name as GET should suffice.\r\n\r\nThe reason that all routes should have names is that, for example, in the action=\"\" attribute of the forms we could refer to the name of the route instead of a link that could change in time. If we refer to the link then when the link will change then all forms that refer that link should be also changed.\r\n\r\nIf the action is set by the route name then in case of a link change that change should be done only in the routes.php file whitout the need to alter code in other places.\r\n\r\nShould I change the existing code to use named routes?',NULL,NULL,5,29,4,NULL,29,2,'2014-08-06 20:44:27','2014-12-18 11:43:34','2014-08-06',0,NULL,NULL,767,1,2,0,'2014-12-18 11:43:34'),(768,4,50,'Multiple templates','The RA will have multiple templates?\r\n\r\nIf so, there are few things to be modified in the base controller to allow multiple templates with one set up as default template.',NULL,NULL,5,29,4,NULL,29,2,'2014-08-06 20:59:17','2014-12-18 11:43:30','2014-08-06',0,NULL,NULL,768,1,2,0,'2014-12-18 11:43:30'),(773,1,50,'osTicket','osTicket should have it\'s own composer package and stay out of the public folder.\r\n\r\nFor that a dedicated composer / laravel package should be created. Keeping a lot of code in the public folder which corespond more to the assets of t